Many states, including the U.S., may
be unable to fulfill development aid pledges because of the euro
crisis and the economic slowdown,  Bild Zeitung  reported, citing
Economic Cooperation Minister Dirk Niebel.  Niebel said  Germany  will fulfill its pledges, which in 2012
amount to 164 million euros ($212 million), the newspaper
